context: Kanye Omari West was born on June 8, 1977 in <a1_0>Atlanta<a1_0/>, Georgia. His parents divorced when he was three and he and his mother moved to Chicago, Illinois. His father, Ray West, is a former Black Panther and was one of the first black photojournalists at The Atlanta Journal-Constitution. Ray West was later a Christian counselor, and in 2006, opened the <a2_0>Good Water Store and Café<a2_0/> in Lexington Park, Maryland with startup capital from his son. West's mother, Dr. Donda C. (Williams) West, was a professor of <a0_0>English<a0_0/> at Clark Atlanta University, and the Chair of the English Department at <a3_0>Chicago State University<a3_0/> before retiring to serve as his manager. West was raised in a middle-class background, attending <a4_0>Polaris High School<a4_0/> in suburban Oak Lawn, Illinois after living in Chicago.
